summary: This document is an email from Alaska Airlines' legal team to the FBI stating they have no responsive records for a federal grand jury subpoena related to Ghislaine Maxwell for the specific time frame requested. It indicates law enforcement was seeking travel records involving Maxwell in early 2020.

events.title: Federal Grand Jury Subpoena Issued

events.title: Alaska Airlines Response to Subpoena
events.description: Alaska Airlines' legal team responded to the FBI, stating they had no responsive records for the subpoena regarding Ghislaine Maxwell for the requested time frame.

keyFacts: A federal grand jury subpoena was issued on or before January 23, 2020, seeking records from Alaska Airlines related to Ghislaine Maxwell.
Alaska Airlines conducted a search and found no responsive records for the specific time frame requested in the subpoena.
The FBI was actively investigating Ghislaine Maxwell's travel patterns as of early 2020, as evidenced by this subpoena for airline records.
